Description: This is a fender Roadhouse body with a Mighty Might 7.25-10 compound radius, soft V to C profile maple neck in satin finish.I do not have the original neck.Please note that the tuners are vintage white pearl to match the original pickgaurd.The body is a wonderfull vintage white in great condition except for one small chip about the size of a pencil point that I tried as best I could to show in the pic.The body is currently set up with a great set of EMG SA pups.Please note the upgraded bridge saddles, all other components of the bridge/trem block are original.Please note the black input jack, the chrome original is not show but included.The whammy bar is included but not shown in pics.The EMG-SA pickup combines the attributes of the early Strat sound but with an added midrange response and higher output, giving it bell-like ringing harmonics and increased sustain. One single Alnico bar magnet delivers classic overdrive with a smooth midrange distortion, while still retaining the familiar high end of a single-coil pickup. These characteristics provide greater versatility than what is normally found in single-coil pickups. The internal preamp rejects every bit of hum and buzz for noiseless operation. The pups do a great job of mimicking Fat 50's. The original Three Texas Special single-coil pickups wired for versatilityV6 rotary switch delivers six distinct onboard-preamp tone settingsS-1 switch built into the volume knob bypasses the preamp is included the sale and are in brand new condition.This has been recently set up with 10's and was a project that I fell in love with, she plays & sounds wonderfully but I'm moving onto another project.
